The Daily Beast obtained a US Government cable describing a communications ploy apparently originating at the National Security Council, and citing the strategy as "All About China".
We have been told to try to convey this message in any way possible, including press conferences and TV appearances. "Media outlets like Politico, Foreign Policy and Bloomberg have claimed that China's efforts to send aid to countries affected by the virus are part of a propaganda to gain global influence.
