The planned NATO military exercise "Defender 2020" in Germany, Poland and the Baltic States, the largest NATO war exercise since the end of the Cold War, will be conducted on a reduced scale.
Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament Secretary-General Kate Hudson criticized the Defender 2020 exercise: "In the current public health crisis, it endangers the lives not only of the troops of the United States and the various European countries involved, but also those of the people of the countries in which they operate".
On 14 March 2020, President Hassan Rouhani of Iran wrote a public letter to world leaders asking for help, saying his country is having difficulty combating the outbreak due to lack of access to international markets as a result of US sanctions against Iran.The outbreak prompted demands for the United States to adopt common social policies in other rich countries, such as universal health care, universal child care, paid family leave and higher levels of funding for public health.
